{"title_page": "Nithya Menen", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{pp-move-indef|small=yes}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Nithya Menen <!--Do not change to Menon. She and multiple reliable sources confirmed Menen, which is an acronym of her parents names - unusual, yes -->\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1988|04|08}}<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/happy-birthday-nithya-menen-lesser-known-facts-rare-unseen-photos-ok-kanmani-actress-628454 Happy Birthday Nithya Menen: Lesser Known Facts, Rare and Unseen Photos of 'OK Kanmani' Actress]. Ibtimes.co.in (8 April 2015). Retrieved on 21 October 2017.</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]<ref name=\"newscrunch\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.newscrunch.in/2016/09/melting-pot-india-i-am-not-kerala-kutti-kannada-my-mother-tongue-says-Kerwls-girl-nithya |title=Melting pot India: I am not a Kerala kutti, Kannada my mother tongue, says Bangalore girl Nithya Menon |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815102819/http://www.newscrunch.in/2016/09/melting-pot-india-i-am-not-kerala-kutti-kannada-my-mother-tongue-says-bangalore-girl-nithya |archive-date=15 August 2017}}</ref>\n| nationality        = [[India]]n\n| home town          = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Mount Carmel College, Bangalore|Mount Carmel College ]]\n| occupation         = [[Actress]], [[playback singer]]\n| yearsactive        = 2006\u2013present\n| known_for          = \n| home_town          = Bangalore\n}}\n\n'''Nithya Menen'''<!-- it's reliably sourced that her surname is spelled Menen!! Don't change it!! --><ref name=\"rediff1\">{{cite web|url=http://tfpc.in/nithya-menon-latest-photos/|title=Nithya Menen Latest Photos|publisher=TFPC|date=17 April 2015 |accessdate=17 April 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"rediff5\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-nithya-menen-on-ala-modalaindi/20110120.htm |title='I'm not inclined towards commercial cinema'|publisher=Rediff|date=20 January 2011 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"thehindu1\">{{cite news|author=Narasimham, M. L. |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article528184.ece |title=Arts / Cinema : Charm of romantic comedies |work=The Hindu |date=22 July 2010 |accessdate=7 April 2011 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref> (born 8 April 1988)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Nithya-Menen|title=Nithya Menen: Movies, Photos, Videos, News, Biography & Birthday {{!}} eTimes|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref> is an [[Indian film]] [[actress]] and [[playback singer]] who appears in [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]], [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]], [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]], [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] and [[Bollywood|Hindi films]] where she has established herself as a leading actress. She is recipient of three [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] for the Telugu films ''[[Gunde Jaari Gallanthayyinde]]'', ''[[Malli Malli Idi Rani Roju]]'' and ''[[Mersal (film)|Mersal]]'' in Tamil.\n\nAfter making her acting debut as a child in the 1998 [[English film]] ''The Monkey Who Knew Too Much,'' Nithya started her acting career by playing supporting role in [[Kannada film]] ''[[7 O' Clock]]. S''he made her debut in leading role in [[Malayalam]] with ''[[Akasha Gopuram]],'' [[Telugu language|Telugu]] with ''[[Ala Modalaindi]]'' and [[Tamil language|Tamil]] with ''[[180 (2011 Indian film)|180]]''. In August 2019, she made her [[Bollywood]] debut with ''[[Mission Mangal]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nNithya Menen was born in [[Banashankari]], [[Bangalore]]. She studied journalism at the [[Manipal University]].<ref name=\"Youtube\">{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=gwRzgTNXuR4&t=736s#menu }}</ref>  She once said in an interview that she never wished to become an actress but a journalist,<ref name=\"rediff2\">{{cite web|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/mar/03/slide-show-1-south-nithya-menon-on-apoorvaragam.htm |title='I love to do intelligent films like Kerala Cafe' |publisher=Rediff.com |date=3 March 2010 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-03/news-interviews/29374848_1_first-film-telugu-film-siddharth |title=Nithya plays a journalist in next|work=The Times of India|date=3 April 2011 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> but ultimately found journalism unappealing, so she pivoted to filmmaking,<ref name=\"indiatimes1\"/><ref name=\"indiatimes2\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-22/news-interviews/28625193_1_films-ala-modalaindi-nithya-menon |title=I forced myself to learn Telugu: Nithya|work=The Times of India|date=22 February 2011 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-07-30/news-interviews/28310303_1_film-nithya-menon-actress |title=I've never wanted to be an actress: Nithya|work=The Times of India|date=30 July 2010 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> and enrolled in a [[cinematography]] course at the [[Film and Television Institute of India|Film and Television Institute of India]] at Pune. During the [[educational entrance examination|school's entrance exam]], she met [[B. V. Nandini Reddy]], who convinced Menen to take up acting.<ref name=\"indiatimes1\" /> Reddy would later turn director and sign Nithya for a lead role in her first Telugu film. Even though Menen's mother tongue is Malayalam, she can speak all South Indian languages.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DfCYCbJcjic</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===1998===\nNithya appeared first on screen as a child artist when she was eight<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starsunfolded.com/nithya-menen/|title=Nithya Menen Height, Weight, Age, Affairs, Biography & More \u00bb StarsUnfolded|website=StarsUnfolded|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref> in the Indian English language film, ''The Monkey Who Knew Too Much'' (1998), playing the younger sister to [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]]'s character.<ref>Gupta, Rinku (6 April 2011) [http://newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/article373258.ece Nithya Menen enters Kollywood]. The New Indian Express. Retrieved on 29 April 2016.</ref> In 2006, she started her acting career in a supporting role with the [[Kannada]] film ''[[7 O' Clock]]'' directed by Kannada's top cinematographer Santosh Rai Pataje.<ref>[http://m.indiaglitz.com/nithya-menon-in-jogaiah-kannada-news-66798.html Nithya Menon in \u0091Jogaiah\u0092-Kannada Movie News]. M.indiaglitz.com (18 May 2011). Retrieved on 29 April 2016.</ref> The 2008 off-beat film ''[[Aakasha Gopuram]]'', directed by National Film Award-winning director [[K. P. Kumaran]], marked her Malayalam debut in leading role in which she was paired with [[Mohanlal]]. She was in the midst of her 12th class exams when she was offered the role, after Mohanlal had spotted her on the front cover of a tourism magazine, Stark World Kerala.<ref name=\"rediff1\"/><ref name=\"rediff2\"/> Her performance was well received, with critics writing that she shows \"sparkle in her debut venture\" and \"makes her entry in an impressive role\",<ref name=\"india\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/malayalam/review/10003.html |title=Akasha Gopuram Malayalam Movie Review |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=25 August 2008 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"sify\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/aakasha-gopuram-review-malayalam-14744808.html |title=Movie Review:Aakasha Gopuram|publisher=Sify |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> though the film, based on the Norwegian play ''[[The Master Builder]]'', got mixed reviews and was a financial failure.<ref name=\"india\"/><ref name=\"sify\"/> She next made a comeback into Kannada films with the super hit film ''[[Josh (2009 Kannada film)|Josh]]''. She played a supporting role in the film, which received rave reviews,<ref>{{cite news|author=Kumar, G. S. |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/kannada/movie-reviews/Josh/movie-review/4384074.cms |title=Josh movie review|work=The Times of India |date=10 April 2009 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/kannada/review/10497.html |title=Josh Kannada Movie Review |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=14 April 2009 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/kannada/reviews/2009/movie-josh-review-130409.html |title=Movie Josh Review &#124; Akshay Alok Jagannath|publisher=One India |date=13 April 2009 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> and became a commercial success as well, with her performance garnering her a nomination in the Best Supporting Actress category at the [[57th Filmfare Awards South]].\n\n===2010: Telugu debut and breakthrough===\nIn 2011, her first release was Nandini Reddy's [[romantic comedy]] ''[[Ala Modalaindi]]'', which was Nithya's maiden Telugu venture as well.<ref name=\"thehindu1\"/> The film opened to favourable reviews by critics and turned out to become a [[sleeper hit]],<ref name=\"rediff3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-nandini-reddys-debut-film-ala-modalaindi/20110406.htm |title=Overwhelmed by response for Ala Modalaindi|publisher=Rediff|accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> while Nithya received critical praise for her performance. ''Idlebrain''{{'}}s Jeevi in his review cited that she \"epitomized Nitya character with her fabulous performance\", \"looks beautiful in all kinds of dresses\" and was \"the best debut in recent years of Telugu cinema after [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]] in ''[[Ye Maaya Chesave|YMC]]''\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-alamodalaindi.html |title=Ala Modalaindi film review \u2013 Telugu cinema Review \u2013 Nani & Nitya Menon |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=21 January 2011 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> while another critic wrote that she was a \"charming find\" and \"...quite the [[Genelia D'Souza|Genelia]] replacement that our cinema so badly needs right now.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fullhyderabad.com/profile/movies/4021/2/ala-modalaindi-movie-review |title=Ala Modalaindi Review - Ala Modalaindi Movie Review on fullhyd.com |publisher=Fullhyderabad.com |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> She eventually won the [[Nandi Award for Best Actress]] for her performance and received a nomination for [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Telugu|Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] at the [[59th Filmfare Awards South]].<ref>[http://www.idlebrain.com/news/2000march20/nandiawards2010.html Nandi awards 2010 announced \u2013 Telugu cinema news]. Idlebrain.com (5 August 2011). Retrieved 10 August 2011.</ref> Further more, she also sang two songs for the soundtrack album of the film, tuned by [[Kalyani Malik]].<ref name=\"cinegoer1\">{{cite web|url= https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=gwRzgTNXuR4&t=739s/ |title=Nithya Menon &#124; BV Nandini Reddy \u2013 Interviews |publisher=CineGoer.com |date=21 November 2010 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/jun/21/south-ala-modalaindi-first-look.htm |title=First look: Nandini Reddy's Ala Modalaindi |publisher=Rediff.com |date=21 June 2010 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> Nandini Reddy, later, went on to describe Nithya as \"the discovery of the decade\".<ref name=\"rediff3\"/> Following ''Ala Modalaindi'', she starred in [[Santosh Sivan]]'s historical fiction ''[[Urumi (film)|Urumi]]'' as part of an [[ensemble cast]].<ref name=\"rediff4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-nithya-menon-on-urumi/20110331.htm |title=Urumi was difficult to shoot for|publisher=Rediff|date=31 March 2011 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> She portrayed a [[Chirakkal, Kannur|Chirakkal]] princess named Bala, playing the love interest of [[Prabhu Deva]]'s character,<ref name=\"rediff4\"/> which gained positive remarks, with a Sify review claiming that she \"looks pretty and is a scene stealer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/urumi-review-review-malayalam-14966427.html |title=Movie Review:Urumi- Review|publisher=Sify |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> Nithya quoted that much of her character was based on \"Santosh's perception of who I am\", with Sivan stating that he had written that role for her and that only she could play it. She received a nomination for [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Malayalam|Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress]] at the [[59th Filmfare Awards South]]<ref name=\"rediff4\"/> She next appeared in ad-filmmaker Jayendra's bilingual venture ''[[180 (2011 Tamil film)|180]]''/''Nootrenbadhu'', made and released in Tamil and Telugu, in which she played a [[photo journalist]] named Vidhya.<ref name=\"rediff.com\">[http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-nithya-menen/20110622.htm Nithya Menen: The character I play in 180 is like me \u2013 Rediff.com Movies]. Rediff.com (22 June 2011). Retrieved 10 August 2011.</ref> She described the character as \"bubbly, full of life, nosey, wide-eyed and innocent in life\" and to be similar to herself.<ref name=\"rediff.com\"/> Later the year, she was seen in [[Sibi Malayil]]'s ''[[Violin (2011 film)|Violin]]'' in Malayalam and the [[Gautham Menon]]-produced ''[[Veppam]]'' in Tamil.\n\n=== 2012: Recognition ===\nHer first 2012 release was the Telugu romance film ''[[Ishq (2012 film)|Ishq]]'' with Nitin Reddy. She received the CineMAA Award for Best Actress(jury) while received best actress nomination at the same event and at the SIIMA Awards. She acted in ''[[Karmayogi (2012 film)|Karmayogi]]'', a Malayalam adaptation of [[Shakespeare]]'s ''[[Hamlet]]''. For the Kannada film ''Aidondla Aidu'' she had sung and also choreographed one of the songs, titled \"Payasa\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-nithya-menen/20110622.htm |title=I am enjoying my own space |publisher=Rediff|date=1 July 2011 |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> She was seen in two Malayalam projects, [[T. K. Rajeev Kumar]]'s ''[[Thalsamayam Oru Penkutty]]'', in which she portrayed a village woman whose daily life is filmed and broadcast as a reality show for a month,<ref>{{cite news|agency=TNN|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-10-31/news-interviews/30341377_1_kumar-s-thalsamayam-oru-pennkutty-film-shweta-menon|title=When life becomes a TV show for Nithya Menen|work=The Times of India|date=31 October 2011|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref> and ''[[Ustad Hotel]] directed by [[Anwar Rasheed]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Sidhardhan, Sanjith |agency=TNN|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-11-13/news-interviews/30398032_1_producers-nithya-menen-film|title=Nithya Menen forges ahead|work=The Times of India|date=13 November 2011|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n===2013: Critical acclaim===\nIn 2013, she starred in three Telugu films, ''[[Okkadine]]'', ''[[Jabardasth (film)|Jabardasth]]'' and ''[[Gunde Jaari Gallanthayyinde]]'' and one Kannada movie [[Myna (film)|Mynaa]]. She played a character with two shades in ''Gunde Jaari Gallanthayyinde'' and she dubbed for her as well as for the character of her co-star [[Isha Talwar]]. For this movie, she received her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Telugu|Filmfare Award for Best Telugu Actress]] at the [[61st Filmfare Awards South]].<ref>[http://idlebrain.com/news/today/nityamenen-ishatalwardubbing.html Nitya Menen dubs for Isha Talwar in GJG \u2013 Telugu cinema news]. Idlebrain.com (20 April 2013). Retrieved 19 June 2013.</ref> In 2014, she made a cameo in the Malayalam movie ''[[Bangalore Days]]'', which became the highest grosser of that year.<ref>[http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/No-Hyderabad-days-yet/articleshow/45781766.cms No Hyderabad days yet]. Bangalore Mirror (6 January 2015). Retrieved on 30 April 2015.</ref> Her Kannada film ''[[Myna (film)|Mynaa]]'' which won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Film \u2013 Kannada]]<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/kannada/article/79206.html Myna reality check! \u2013 Kannada Movie News]. Indiaglitz.com (12 March 2012). Retrieved on 29 April 2016.</ref> in which she plays a character of a physically challenged girl, became a huge blockbuster hit completing 100 days in many centers across Karnataka and her performance was well praised by the critics. She has paired up with [[Sharwanand]] for the 2015 Telugu movie ''[[Malli Malli Idi Rani Roju]]''. Her performance was well praised by the critics eventually receiving her [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress South]], [[Nandi Special Jury Award]] and also receiving her second nomination at Filmfare. With this Nithya became the first Telugu actress ever to win Critics Award & the Best Actress Award at Filmfare. She did a minor role in the film ''[[S/O Satyamurthy]]'', directed by [[Trivikram]]'. She appeared opposite ''[[Dulquer Salmaan]]'' in two films in 2015, ''[[100 Days of Love]]'', a romantic Malayalam film and ''[[OK Kanmani]]'', bilingual film directed by [[Mani Ratnam]]'. Dulquer and Nithya's on-screen chemistry was praised in the reviews of both films. For OK Kanmani, she received her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Tamil|Filmfare Award for Best Tamil Actress]] nomination.<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/100-days-love-movie-review-breezy-romantic-comedy-flick-featuring-dulquer-salmaan-nithya-menen-626817 '100 Days of Love' Movie Review: A Breezy Romantic Comedy Flick Featuring Dulquer Salmaan, Nithya Menen]. Ibtimes.co.in (20 March 2015). Retrieved on 30 April 2015.</ref><ref>[http://www.aptoday.com/moviereviews/ok-bangaram/108/ Review : Ok Bangaram / Ok Kanmani / O Kadhal Kamnai Movie, Story, Public Talk]. Aptoday.com. Retrieved on 30 April 2015.</ref>\n\n===2016===\n{{cleanup|section|reason=Not written from a [[WP:NPOV|neutral point of view]]. Tone of prose inconsistent with an encyclopedia.|date=April 2020}}\nIn 2016, she starred in three [[Tamil language|Tamil]] films, [[24 (2016 film)|24]] opposite [[Suriya]] was opened to high critical acclaim, with critics praising her screen presence and garnered her a [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Tamil]] nomination at 64th [[Filmfare Awards South]], Another [[K. S. Ravikumar]]'s bilingual project titled [[Kotigobba 2]] opposite [[Sudeep]] while both versions opened to positive reviews, Kannada version became Blockbuster and Tamil version turned out to be a sleeper hit at Box Office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2015/nithya-menon-to-romance-kiccha-sudeep-in-kotigobba-2-192438.html|title=Nithya Menon To Romance Kichcha Sudeep In 'Kotigobba 2'|publisher=Filmibeat|date=30 July 2015}}</ref> later she starred opposite [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]] in a SciFi thriller [[Iru Mugan]] in which she had a limited screen presence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/iru-mugan/movie-review/54218501.cms|title=Iru Mugan Movie Review {3/5}: Critic Review of Iru Mugan by Times of India|publisher=|via=timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> In Telugu she starred in two films, [[okka Ammayi Thappa]] opposite [[Sundeep Kishan]] opened to negative reviews and tanked at box office, Followed by [[Janatha Garage]] opposite [[Jr. NTR]] opened to positive reviews, though her role is limited but brought raves from critics and latter was commercially successful at box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/janathagarage.html|title=Janatha Garage review by jeevi - Telugu cinema review  -  NTR, Mohanlall, Samantha & Nithya Menen|website=www.idlebrain.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/janatha-garage/movie-review/53960106.cms|title=Janatha Garage Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India|website=indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Her only release was a [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film [[Mersal (film)|Mersal]] opposite [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] opened to critical Acclaim with praising portrayal of her character \"Aishwarya Vetrimaran\" as a loyal wife by critics and Audience alike and the film turned out be a Blockbuster at the box office and garnered her a [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Tamil]] at ''[[65th Filmfare Awards South]]'' .<ref>{{cite web|url=https://regional.pinkvilla.com/tamil/news/nithya-menen-gets-candid-about-her-role-in-vijay-starrer-mersal-my-character-is-the-emotional-pillar-in-the-film/|title=Nithya Menen gets candid about her role in Vijay starrer Mersal: My character is the emotional pillar in the film|website=pinkvilla.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india.com/showbiz/mersal-movie-review-vijay-steals-the-show-with-his-amazing-performance-2540302/|title=Mersal Movie Review: Critics Give A Thumbs Up To Vijay's Film|first=Leona|last=Nathan|date=18 October 2017|website=india.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, her first release was [[Nani (actor)|Nani]]'s Production venture an anthology psychological thriller [[Awe (film)|Awe]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/nanis-film-awe-first-look-out-telugu-news-201461|title=Nani's film: 'Awe' First Look out - Telugu Movie News - IndiaGlitz.com|website=indiaglitz.com}}</ref> In which she played one of the couple alongside [[Eesha Rebba]] who try to get approval of their lesbian relationship from latter's parents. Later the film was opened to unanimous critical acclaim with critics praising menen's performance as screen lighting with a brief and impactful role.\n\nHer next release was VK Prakash's ''[[Praana]]'' which marks her comeback to [[Malayalam]] industry after 2015's romantic flick [[100 days of love]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/malayalam/news/2017/nithya-menen-nithya-menon-is-back-malayalam-cinema-after-brief-break-268625.html|title=WOW! Nithya Menen Is Back To Malayalam After A Brief Break!|date=10 October 2017|website=filmibeat.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/nithya-menen-plays-a-english-writer-battling-intolerance-in-vk-prakashs-multi-lingual/articleshow/60971947.cms|title=Nithya Menen plays an English writer battling intolerance in VK Prakash's multi-lingual - Times of India|website=indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n\nShe made her [[Hindi]] debut with ''[[Mission Mangal]]'' alongside [[Akshay Kumar]].\n\n==Filmography==\n<!--Do not split this into separate article without establishing consensus through discussion-->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Language\n! Notes\n|-\n|1998\n| ''The Monkey Who Knew Too Much''\n|| Younger sister to Tabu || [[Indian English]] ||Child artist\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Seven O' Clock]]'' \n|| Anu || [[Kannada]] ||Debut film\n \n|-\n| 2008 \n| ''[[Akasha Gopuram]]'' \n|| Hilda Varghese || [[Malayalam]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2009 \n|''[[Josh (2009 Kannada film)|Josh]]''\n || Meera || [[Kannada]] || Nominated - [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Kannada ]]\n|-\n| ''[[Vellathooval]]'' \n|| Jiya || rowspan=\"5\" |[[Malayalam]] ||\n|-\n| ''[[Kerala Cafe]]'' \n|| Nithya ||\n|-\n|''[[Angel John]]'' \n|| Sofia ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2010 \n| ''[[Apoorvaragam]]'' \n|| Nancy ||\n|-\n| ''[[Anwar (2010 film)|Anwar]]''\n || Asna ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2011 \n| ''[[Aidondla Aidu]]'' \n|| Gowri  || [[Kannada]] ||\n|-\n|''[[Ala Modalaindi]]''\n || Nithya || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] || [[Nandi Award for Best Actress]] <br> Nominated - [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Telugu]] <br> Nominated - [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Playback Singer - Telugu ]]\n|-\n| ''[[Urumi (film)|Urumi]]'' \n|| Chirakkal Bala || [[Malayalam]] || Nominated - [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Malayalam]] \n|-\n| ''[[180 (2011 Indian film)|180]]'' \n|rowspan=\"2\"| Vidya ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]||\n|-\n|''[[Nootrenbadhu]]''\n|[[Tamil language|Tamil]]|| Nominated - [[Vijay Award for Best Actress]]\n|-\n|''[[Violin (2011 film)|Violin]]'' \n|| Angel ||[[Malayalam]] || Nominated - [[Asianet Film Awards| Asianet Film Awards for Best Actress]]\n|-\n|''[[Veppam]]'' \n|| Revathy ||[[Tamil language|Tamil]]||\n|-\n|''[[Makaramanju]]'' \n||Model ||[[Malayalam]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\"|2012\n|''[[Ishq (2012 film)|Ishq]]'' \n|| Priya ||[[Telugu language|Telugu]]|| \n|-\n|''[[Thalsamayam Oru Penkutty]]'' \n|| Manjula Ayyapan || rowspan=\"6\" | [[Malayalam]] ||\n|-\n|''[[Karmayogi (2012 film)|Karmayogi]]'' \n|| Moonumani ||\n|-\n|''[[Ustad Hotel]]'' \n|| Shahana ||\n|-\n|''[[Doctor Innocent Aanu]]''\n || Anna||\n|-\n|''[[Bachelor Party (2012 film)|Bachelor Party]]''\n || Neethu ||\n|-\n|''[[Poppins]]'' \n||Ammu ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2013 \n| ''[[Okkadine]]''\n|| Shailaja || rowspan=\"2\" | [[Telugu language|Telugu]] ||\n|-\n| ''[[Jabardasth (film)|Jabardasth]]'' \n|| Saraswati ||\n|-\n| ''[[Myna (film)|Myna]]'' \n|| Myna || [[Kannada]] ||\n|-\n|''[[Gunde Jaari Gallanthayyinde]]'' \n|| Shravani || [[Telugu language|Telugu]]|| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Telugu]] <br> Nominated - [[SIIMA Award for Best Actress - Telugu ]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014 \n| ''[[Malini 22 Palayamkottai]]''\n|| Malini ||[[Tamil language|Tamil]]||| Nominated -[[Vijay Award for Best Actress]]\n|-\n|''[[Bangalore Days]]'' \n|| Natasha Francis || [[Malayalam]] || Cameo appearance\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2015 \n| ''[[Malli Malli Idi Rani Roju]]'' \n|| Nazira || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] 