{"title_page": "The Caverns at Natural Bridge", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|text = [[Natural Bridge Caverns|Natural Bridge Caverns (Texas)]]}}\n{{Advert|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox cave\n| name =The Caverns at Natural Bridge\n| other_name = Natural Bridge Caverns\n| photo =\n| photo_width =\n| photo_caption =\n| map = Shenandoah Valley#USA Virginia#USA\n| relief = 1\n| map_width =\n| map_caption =\n| map_alt =\n| location = 6477 S Lee Hwy, Natural Bridge, VA 24578\n| coords = {{coord|37|38|8.7288|N|79|32|29.9364|W|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| coords_ref =\n| land_registry_number =\n| grid_ref_UK =\n| grid_ref_Ireland =\n| grid_ref =\n| depth =\n| length =\n| height_variation =\n| elevation =\n| discovery =\n| geology =\n| entrance_count =\n| entrance_list =\n| difficulty =\n| hazards =\n| access =\n| show_cave =\n| show_cave_length =\n| lighting =\n| visitors =\n| features = Colossal Dome Room, Mirror Lake, Well Room, Canyon Room\n| survey =\n| survey_format =\n| website = {{url|https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html}}\n}}\n\n'''The Caverns at Natural Bridge''' is a commercial [[show cave]] in the [[Shenandoah Valley]] of [[Virginia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Caverns at Natural Bridge |url=https://www.virginia.org/Listings/OutdoorsAndSports/CavernsatNaturalBridge/ |website=Virginia Is for Lovers |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> Discovered in the early 1900s, it was opened to the public in 1977. <ref>{{cite web |title=The Caverns at Natural Bridge |url=https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html |website=Natural Bridge Historic Hotel & Conference Center |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> The Caverns are home to a unique species of beetle called the [[Natural Bridge Cave Beetle|Natural Bridge Cave Beetle (Pseudanophthalmus pontis]] ).<ref>{{Cite book|last=Roble|first=Steven M.|title=Natural Heritage Resources of Virginia:\nRare Animals.|publisher=Virginia Department of Conservation and Recreation, Division of Natural Heritage|year=2016|isbn=|location=Richmond, Virginia|pages=25}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe temperature remains a cool 54\u00b0F (12\u00b0C).<ref>{{cite web |title=The Caverns at Natural Bridge |url=https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html |website=Natural Bridge Historic Hotel & Conference Center |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> The Caverns feature many unique structures including the Colossal Dome Room, Mirror Lake, Well Room, and the Canyon Room.\n\n==Geology==\nThe Shenandoah Valley is underlain with limestone and also has [[karst topography]], forming caves throughout the region. Rainwater becomes slightly acidic as it seeps through the soil. The acid slowly erodes the calcium carbonate, the main component of limestone, creating caves, sinkholes and springs throughout the landscape. There are many cave and caverns throughout the surrounding area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.virginiaplaces.org/cave/|title=Caves and Springs in Virginia|website=www.virginiaplaces.org|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* {{official website|https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html}}\n\n{{Caves in Virginia}}\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|text = [[Natural Bridge Caverns|Natural Bridge Caverns (Texas)]]}}\n{{Advert|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox cave\n| name =The Caverns at Natural Bridge\n| other_name = Natural Bridge Caverns\n| photo =\n| photo_width =\n| photo_caption =\n| map = Shenandoah Valley#USA Virginia#USA\n| relief = 1\n| map_width =\n| map_caption =\n| map_alt =\n| location = 6477 S Lee Hwy, Natural Bridge, VA 24578\n| coords = {{coord|37|38|8.7288|N|79|32|29.9364|W|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| coords_ref =\n| land_registry_number =\n| grid_ref_UK =\n| grid_ref_Ireland =\n| grid_ref =\n| depth =\n| length =\n| height_variation =\n| elevation =\n| discovery =\n| geology =\n| entrance_count =\n| entrance_list =\n| difficulty =\n| hazards =\n| access =\n| show_cave =\n| show_cave_length =\n| lighting =\n| visitors =\n| features = Colossal Dome Room, Mirror Lake, Well Room, Canyon Room\n| survey =\n| survey_format =\n| website = {{url|https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html}}\n}}\n\n'''The Caverns at Natural Bridge''' is a commercial [[show cave]] in the [[Shenandoah Valley]] of [[Virginia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Caverns at Natural Bridge |url=https://www.virginia.org/Listings/OutdoorsAndSports/CavernsatNaturalBridge/ |website=Virginia Is for Lovers |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> Discovered in the early 1900s, it was opened to the public in 1977. <ref>{{cite web |title=The Caverns at Natural Bridge |url=https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html |website=Natural Bridge Historic Hotel & Conference Center |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> The Caverns are home to a unique species of beetle called the [[Natural Bridge Cave Beetle]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Description==\nThe temperature remains a cool 54\u00b0F (12\u00b0C).<ref>{{cite web |title=The Caverns at Natural Bridge |url=https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html |website=Natural Bridge Historic Hotel & Conference Center |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> The Caverns feature many unique structures including the Colossal Dome Room, Mirror Lake, Well Room, and the Canyon Room.\n\n==Geology==\nThe Shenandoah Valley is underlain with limestone and also has [[karst topography]], forming caves throughout the region. Rainwater becomes slightly acidic as it seeps through the soil. The acid slowly erodes the calcium carbonate, the main component of limestone, creating caves, sinkholes and springs throughout the landscape. There are many cave and caverns throughout the surrounding area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.virginiaplaces.org/cave/|title=Caves and Springs in Virginia|website=www.virginiaplaces.org|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* {{official website|https://www.naturalbridgeva.com/caverns.html}}